  <notes>I'm sure it had some small measure to do with the fact that we were in the tourist quarter where things tended towards fried, but it seemed that remoulade was an ubuquitous condiment in New Orleans.  Its a more refined tartar sauce  

While it seems more suited for fried food, it goes pretty nicely with the shrimp and seems to have legs.  Hilary dislikes taragon so we exchange it for thyme which can go in dry, as could the tarragon.</notes>
